📝 Guide: Exploring Websites in Python (Interactive Mode)

1. Open Python Interactive Mode

In the terminal, type:

python3


You will see the interactive prompt: >>>.

2. Import the Requests library
>>> import requests

3. Access a website
>>> site = requests.get("http://google.com.br")

4. View page content
>>> site.content

5. View HTTP headers
>>> site.headers

6. Check response status
>>> site.status_code

7. Check the web server used by the site
>>> site.headers['Server']

8. Exit interactive mode
>>> exit()

👉 What you learned here

requests.get() → sends an HTTP request to the site.

.content → returns the HTML content of the page.

.headers → returns the HTTP headers.

.status_code → returns the HTTP status code.

.headers['Server'] → identifies the web server used by the site.

Python interactive mode is useful for quick tests without creating files.
